<section>
    <h2>Fun Facts About Dolphins</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Dolphins live in social groups called pods.</li>
        <li>Dolphins are highly intelligent and can solve problems and communicate.</li>
        <li>Dolphins are mammals, just like humans, and give birth to live young.</li>
        <li>Dolphins often use tools and have unique vocalizations.</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Why Dolphins Are Special</h2>
    <p>As a child, I was fascinated by how dolphins live, work, and play together in their pods. Their intelligence, social nature, and the fact that they are mammals, just like us, made me feel a special connection to them. I loved learning all I could about these beautiful creatures, and I hope to share that passion with my daughter one day!</p>
</section>

